race.comment: FLYING BATTY (3) held her own to the line last start and filled a minor placing, beaten only 0.8 lengths (26.00) behind Anchor Cranker at Geelong. Winning claims. PAW QUANDA (2) dropped out early but hit the line hard, charging into third and beaten 7 lengths win (23.77) at Horsham in Grade 5. Hard to beat again. NOT OUR FAULT (1) has missed the frame the last couple but was a Grade 5 winner three back (29.81) at Sandown over 515m. Well placed here and should do much better. DOCHERTY (8) was in the money last start here at this trip - likely to feature again.
